TITLE: Implementing Double-Click Observer in CKEditor 5
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a custom DoubleClickObserver and listen for double-click events on specific elements (e.g., links) in CKEditor 5. It extends the DomEventObserver class and registers the observer with the editor's view.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/docs/framework/how-tos.md#2025-04-16_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { DomEventObserver } from 'ckeditor5';

class DoubleClickObserver extends DomEventObserver {
	constructor( view ) {
		super( view );

		this.domEventType = 'dblclick';
	}

	onDomEvent( domEvent ) {
		this.fire( domEvent.type, domEvent );
	}
}

// Then use in the editor:
const view = editor.editing.view;
const viewDocument = view.document;

view.addObserver( DoubleClickObserver );

editor.listenTo(
	viewDocument,
	'dblclick',
	( evt, data ) => {
		console.log( 'clicked' );
		// Fire your custom actions here.
	},
	{ context: 'a' }
);
```

