TITLE: Creating AbbreviationCommand in CKEditor 5
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the AbbreviationCommand class, which extends the Command class from CKEditor 5. It implements the execute method to insert an abbreviation into the editor's model.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/docs/tutorials/abbreviation-plugin-tutorial/abbreviation-plugin-level-3.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { Command } from 'ckeditor5';

export default class AbbreviationCommand extends Command {
	execute( { title, abbr } ) {
		const model = this.editor.model;

		model.change( writer => {
			model.insertContent(
