TITLE: Creating Custom Bookmark Toolbar Component
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of a custom plugin that adds a new component to the bookmark toolbar by registering it in the component factory.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/packages/ckeditor5-bookmark/docs/features/bookmarks.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class MyCustomPlugin extends Plugin {
	init() {
		const editor = this.editor;

		editor.ui.componentFactory.add( 'myCustomBookmarkInfo', locale => {
			const button = new ButtonView( locale );
			const bookmarkCommand = editor.commands.get( 'insertBookmark' );

			button.bind( 'isEnabled' ).to( bookmarkCommand, 'value', href => !!href );
			button.bind( 'label' ).to( bookmarkCommand, 'value' );

			button.on( 'execute', () => {
				// Add your custom component logic here
			} );

			return button;
		} );
	}
}
```

