TITLE: Converting Heading Element with Attribute to View Element
DESCRIPTION: This code example converts a heading model element with a level attribute into an h[level] view element based on the attribute's value in CKEditor 5. It uses the 'elementToElement' conversion helper. Requires the editor's conversion API.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/packages/ckeditor5-engine/docs/framework/deep-dive/conversion/downcast.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
editor.conversion
	.for( 'downcast' )
	.elementToElement( {
		model: {
			name: 'heading',
			attributes: [ 'level' ]
		},
		view: ( modelElement, { writer } ) => {
			return writer.createContainerElement(
				'h' + modelElement.getAttribute( 'level' )
			);
		}
	} );
```

