TITLE: Creating and Rendering Parent View with Child Views in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a parent view that contains child views. It demonstrates the view-per-tree organization and how to render and append the resulting DOM structure.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/docs/framework/architecture/ui-library.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class ParentView extends View {
	constructor( locale ) {
		super( locale );

		const childA = new SimpleInputView( locale );
		const childB = new SimpleInputView( locale );

		this.setTemplate( {
			tag: 'div',
			children: [
				childA,
				childB
			]
		} );
	}
}

const parent = new ParentView( locale );

parent.render();

// This will insert <div><input .. /><input .. /></div>.
document.body.appendChild( parent.element );
```

