TITLE: Element to Attribute Conversion: Handling Attribute Values via Callback
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates handling attribute values through a callback for additional processing. It converts `font-size` styles to 'small' or 'big' model attributes based on defined criteria.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/packages/ckeditor5-engine/docs/framework/deep-dive/conversion/helpers/upcast.md#2025-04-16_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
editor.conversion
	.for( 'upcast' )
	.elementToAttribute( {
		view: {
			name: 'span',
			styles: {
				'font-size': /[\s\S]+/
			}
		},
		model: {
			key: 'fontSize',
			value: ( viewElement, conversionApi ) => {
				const fontSize = viewElement.getStyle( 'font-size' );
				const value = fontSize.substr( 0, fontSize.length - 2 );

				if ( value <= 10 ) {
					return 'small';
				} else if ( value > 12 ) {
					return 'big';
				}

				return null;
			}
		}
