TITLE: Converting Elements with Downcast Pipeline in CKEditor 5
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet shows the transition from the old `triggerBy` API to the new syntax for converting elements in the downcast pipeline. The `triggerBy` property, which enabled conversion upon changes of certain attributes or children, is now obsolete. Instead, model attributes and children that trigger reconversion should be specified directly within the `model` property. Dependencies: CKEditor 5 with the conversion API enabled. Key parameter: `model` specifying elements and conditions for reconversion. Outputs: Converted view elements based on changes in model attributes or children.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/docs/updating/update-to-33.md#2025-04-16_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// ❌ The old conversion using obsolete "triggerBy":
editor.conversion.for( 'downcast' ).elementToElement( {
	model: 'myElement',
	view: ( modelElement, { writer } ) => {
		return writer.createContainerElement( 'div', {
			'data-owner-id': modelElement.getAttribute( 'ownerId' ),
			class: `my-element my-element-${ modelElement.getAttribute( 'type' ) }`
		} );
	},
	triggerBy: {
		attributes: [ 'ownerId', 'type' ],
		children: 'childModelElement'
	}
} );

// ✅ The new conversion syntax:
editor.conversion.for( 'downcast' ).elementToElement( {
	model: {
		name: 'myElement',
		attributes: [ 'ownerId', 'type' ],
		children: true
	},
	view: ( modelElement, { writer } ) => {
		// The same converter code.
	}
} );
```

