TITLE: Creating Command for Abbreviation Plugin in CKEditor 5
DESCRIPTION: Implements a command to insert text with abbreviation attributes into the editor model. Handles selection and text insertion with appropriate model attributes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/tests/manual/abbreviation-level-3.md#2025-04-16_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { Command } from '@ckeditor/ckeditor5-core';

export default class Abbreviationommand extends Command {
	execute( value ) {
		const editor = this.editor;
		const selection = editor.model.document.selection;
		const title = value.title;
		const abbr = value.abbr;

		editor.model.change( writer => {
			writer.insertText( abbr, { 'abbreviation': title }, selection.getFirstPosition() );
			for ( const range of selection.getRanges() ) {
				writer.remove( range );
			}
		} );
	}
}
```

