TITLE: Using Event Listeners in CKEditor 5 Plugins
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use event listeners in a CKEditor 5 plugin. It shows listening to command execution and how to block a command's execution using event priorities.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/docs/framework/architecture/core-editor-architecture.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class MyPlugin extends Plugin {
	init() {
		// Make MyPlugin listen to someCommand#execute.
		this.listenTo( someCommand, 'execute', () => {
			console.log( 'someCommand was executed' );
		} );

		// Make MyPlugin listen to someOtherCommand#execute and block it.
		// You listen with a high priority to block the event before
		// someOtherCommand's execute() method is called.
		this.listenTo( someOtherCommand, 'execute', evt => {
			evt.stop();
		}, { priority: 'high' } );
	}

	// Inherited from Plugin:
	destroy() {
		// Removes all listeners added with this.listenTo();
		this.stopListening();
	}
}
```

