TITLE: Defining a Simple Input View in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to define a simple input view class extending the base View class. It sets up observable properties, binds them to DOM attributes and events, and defines a template for rendering.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/docs/framework/architecture/ui-library.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class SimpleInputView extends View {
	constructor( locale ) {
		super( locale );

		// An entry point to binding observables with DOM attributes,
		// events, and text nodes.
		const bind = this.bindTemplate;

		// Views define their interface (state) using observable properties.
		this.set( {
			isEnabled: false,
			placeholder: ''
		} );

		this.setTemplate( {
			tag: 'input',
			attributes: {
				class: [
					'foo',
					// The value of "view#isEnabled" will control the presence
					// of the class.
					bind.if( 'isEnabled', 'ck-enabled' ),
				],

				// The HTML "placeholder" attribute is also controlled by the observable.
				placeholder: bind.to( 'placeholder' ),
				type: 'text'
			},
			on: {
				// DOM "keydown" events will fire the "view#input" event.
				keydown: bind.to( 'input' )
			}
		} );
	}

	setValue( newValue ) {
		this.element.value = newValue;
	}
}
```

