TITLE: Extending CKEditor5 Schema for Abbreviation Support
DESCRIPTION: This code extends the CKEditor5 schema to allow 'abbreviation' attributes in text nodes, an essential step for enabling abbreviation features in the plugin. It updates the `AbbreviationEditing` plugin with schema definitions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/tests/manual/abbreviation-level-3.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// abbreviation/abbreviationediting.js

import { Plugin } from 'ckeditor5';

export default class AbbreviationEditing extends Plugin {
	init() {
		console.log( 'AbbreviationEditing#init() got called' );

		this._defineSchema();                                                  // ADDED
	}

	_defineSchema() {                                                          // ADDED
		const schema = this.editor.model.schema;
		schema.extend( '$text', {
			allowAttributes: [ 'abbreviation' ]
		} );
	}
}
```

