TITLE: Binding Template to Observable Properties in CKEditor 5
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to bind observable properties to a template in a CKEditor 5 `View` class using the `setTemplate()` method. The `bind.to()` and `bind.if()` functions are used to dynamically update the DOM based on the values of the `label`, `isOn`, and `isEnabled` properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/packages/ckeditor5-utils/docs/framework/deep-dive/observables.md#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class Button extends View {
	constructor() {
		super();

		// Previously defined properties.
		// ...

		// This template will have the following symbolic representation in DOM:
		//
		// 	<button class=\"[ck-disabled] ck-[on|off]\" type=\"button\">
		// 		{{ this.label }}
		// 	</button>
		//
		this.setTemplate( {
			tag: 'button',
			attributes: {
				class: [
					// The 'ck-on' and 'ck-off' classes toggle according to the #isOn property.
					bind.to( 'isOn', value => value ? 'ck-on' : 'ck-off' ),

					// The 'ck-enabled' class appears when the #isEnabled property is false.
					bind.if( 'isEnabled', 'ck-disabled', value => !value )
				],
				type: this.type
			},
			children: [
				{
					// The text of the button is bound to the #label property.
					text: bind.to( 'label' )
				}
			]
		} );
	}
}
```

