TITLE: Defining Block Image Schema in CKEditor 5
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the schema for a block image in CKEditor 5. It specifies that the image is allowed in root, can have certain attributes, and disallows content inside.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/packages/ckeditor5-image/tests/manual/imageblock.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
schema.register( 'imageBlock', {
    isObject: true,
    isBlock: true,
    allowWhere: '$block',
    allowAttributes: [ 'src', 'alt' ]
} );

schema.addChildCheck( ( context, childDefinition ) => {
    if ( context.endsWith( 'imageBlock' ) && childDefinition.name != 'caption' ) {
        return false;
    }
} );
```

