TITLE: Styling Form Elements with CSS Grid - CSS
DESCRIPTION: This CSS snippet provides styling for the form and its elements using CSS grid layout. It defines padding for the form and margin at the bottom of the input fields.  Specific grid areas are defined for the input fields and buttons to control their layout within the form.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/tests/manual/abbreviation-level-2.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: css
CODE:
```
/* style.css */

.ck.ck-abbr-form {
	padding: var(--ck-spacing-large);
	display: grid;
	grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
	grid-template-rows: repeat(3, 1fr);
	grid-column-gap: 0px;
	grid-row-gap: var(--ck-spacing-standard);
}

.ck.ck-abbr-form .ck.ck-labeled-field-view:nth-of-type(1) {
	grid-area: 1 / 1 / 2 / 3;
}

.ck.ck-abbr-form .ck.ck-labeled-field-view:nth-of-type(2) {
	grid-area: 2 / 1 / 3 / 3;
}

.ck.ck-abbr-form .ck-button:nth-of-type(1) {
	grid-area: 3 / 1 / 4 / 2;
}

.ck.ck-abbr-form .ck-button:nth-of-type(2) {
	grid-area: 3 / 2 / 4 / 3;
}

```

