TITLE: Method Decoration Implementation in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Implements method decoration for a Button class's focus method to enable event-driven behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/packages/ckeditor5-utils/docs/framework/deep-dive/observables.md#2025-04-16_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class Button extends View {
	constructor() {
		// Setting the template and bindings.
		// ...

		this.decorate( 'focus' );
	}

	/**
	* Focuses the button.
	*
	* @param {Boolean} force When `true`, the button will be focused again, even if already
	* focused in DOM.
	* @returns {Boolean} `true` when the DOM element was focused in DOM, `false` otherwise.
	*/
	focus( force ) {
		console.log( `Focusing button, force argument="${ force }"` );

		// Unless forced, the button will only focus when not already focused.
		if ( force || document.activeElement != this.element ) {
			this.element.focus();

			return true;
		}

		return false;
	}
}
```

