TITLE: Implementing List Dropdown in CKEditor 5
DESCRIPTION: Creates a dropdown menu containing a list of buttons and switch buttons using CKEditor's UI components. Demonstrates how to create a collection of items and add them to a dropdown using the addListToDropdown helper.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ckeditor/ckeditor5/blob/master/docs/framework/architecture/ui-components.md#2025-04-16_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {
    addListToDropdown,
    Collection,
    createDropdown,
    Locale,
    ViewModel
} from 'ckeditor5';

const locale = new Locale();

const collection = new Collection();
collection.add( {
	type: 'button',
	model: new ViewModel( {
		label: 'Button',
		withText: true
	} )
} );
collection.add( {
	type: 'switchbutton',
	model: new ViewModel( {
		label: 'Switch button',
		withText: true
	} )
} );

const listDropdown = createDropdown( locale );
listDropdown.buttonView.set( {
	label: 'List dropdown',
	withText: true
} );
addListToDropdown( listDropdown, collection );
listDropdown.render();

document.getElementById( 'dropdown-list' ).append( listDropdown.element );
```

